dct_alternative_sm: Colton's Northern Italy Austrian, Venice, Piedmont, Tuscany, Aemilia, Marches, Umbria and the State of the Church
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contour lines and hashures.
Covers Lombardy, Venice, Tuscany, Parma, Modena, Lucca, the Papal States and Corsica.
"Entered according to Act of Congress in the year 1855 by J.H. Colton & Co. in the Clerks Office of the District Court for the Southern District of New York."
Text in English on verso: "Italy and the Italian States --N°. III."
